# Testing Conventions

- Use Vitest for test execution.
- Name tests with `.test.ts` / `.test.tsx` (or `.spec.ts` / `.spec.tsx`).
- Keep tests near the code they validate when practical.

# Test Priorities

- Prioritize tests for module logic in `modules/` first.
- Test core business rules and edge cases before UI polish cases.
- Keep page-level tests focused on composition behavior, not module internals.

# Quality Expectations

- New module logic should include tests for happy-path and at least one failure/edge path.
- Tests should be deterministic and avoid hidden global state.
- Mock only external boundaries (network, time, DB) where necessary.

# Commands

- Use workspace and root test scripts already defined in this repo.
- Ensure lint and tests pass locally before opening a PR.
